article_id:791,category_name:Events,title_name:New Prelude Difficulty Added to High Zodiark's Trial!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/b14aa5bcabc36d5e4923ac3f47cb0569.png,message:<div>We&#39;re happy to let you know that a new difficulty, Prelude, was added to High Zodiark&#39;s Trial at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1570773600"></span>.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/b14aa5bcabc36d5e4923ac3f47cb0569.png"></div><div>Zodiark transforms the spite that consumes him into dark mana, spawning bottomless shadows. Use this difficulty to test your skills before you face him!</div><div><br></div><div>・You cannot obtain the epithet by clearing Prelude difficulty.</div><div>・The weekly bonus for Advanced Dragon Trials also applies to High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Prelude.</div><div>・Rewards differ from those for High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Standard and High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Expert.</div><div><br></div><div>Notes:</div><div>1. In order to challenge High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Prelude, a player&#39;s team must have 11,000 might or higher.</div><div>2. Players must have completed Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Master to challenge High Zodiark&#39;s Trial: Prelude.</div><div>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the campaign in order to play co-op.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1570773600,update_time1570160494